videos.headline: Hawaii starts college football season with failed onside kick
videos.description: Hawaii attempts an onside kick on their opening driving, turning the ball over to California.

videos.headline: California scores first TD of season
videos.description: Khalfani Muhammad rushes 34-yards for a touchdown to put California up 7-0 early on Hawaii.

videos.headline: Cameron Walker intercepts pass from Ikaika Woolsey
videos.description: California DB Cameron Walker gets the first turnover of the college football season with an interception.

videos.headline: Hawaii strikes back through the air
videos.description: Ikaika Woodley 39-yd TD pass to Marcus Kemp ties game at 7.

videos.headline: Golden Bears leap for TD
videos.description: California QB Davis Webb connects with WR Chad Hansen for a 17-yard touchdown to put the Golden Bears back on top of Hawaii 14-7.

videos.headline: Hawaii takes off for 53-yard TD
videos.description: Hawaii running back Diocemy Saint Juste takes off 53 yards for a touchdown to tie the game against California at 14.

videos.headline: Matt Anderson gives Cal the lead
videos.description: Cal K Matt Anderson hits a 29 yard field goal giving the Bears a 17-14 lead.

videos.headline: Beast Mode Down Under
videos.description: Former Cal running back Marshawn Lynch on the sideline watching the Bears in Australia.

videos.headline: Anderson makes his 2nd field goal of the game
videos.description: Matt Anderson drills a 22-yard field goal, extending the Cal lead to 20-14.

videos.headline: Chad Hansen's second TD puts Cal up 27-14
videos.description: Cal's Davis Webb throws his second touchdown pass to Chad Hensen, giving Cal a 27-14 lead.

videos.headline: California recovers fumble on kickoff from monster hit
videos.description: Big hit by Cal's Derron Brown causes a fumble on the kickoff that Cal recovers.

videos.headline: Davis Webb powers his way into the end zone
videos.description: Davis Webb accounts for his third touchdown of the half with a yard option keeper.

videos.headline: Sanchez connects on 42 yard field goal
videos.description: California's lead is cut to 17 after the field goal by Hawaii kicker Rigoberto Sanchez

videos.headline: Cal forces a 4th quarter fumble
videos.description: Cal;s Vic Wharton III recovers the fumble by Hawaii's Diocemy Saint Juste.

videos.headline: Muhammad drops easy touchdown
videos.description: Cal RB Khalfani Muhammad could not keep his eyes on the ball as he drops the pass from Davis Webb in the end zone.

videos.headline: Cal extends lead to 20
videos.description: Matt Anderson converts 25-yard field goal to put California ahead 44-24.

videos.headline: Hawaii scores late to cut into Cal lead
videos.description: Hawaii's Paul Harris cuts through the Cal defense for a 15 yard touchdown run.

videos.headline: Webb carries Cal past Hawaii in college football opener
videos.description: Davis Webb throws four touchdowns, on 38-of-54 passing and 441 yards in California's 51-31 win over Hawaii.
